<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<interface>
  <requires lib="gtk+" version="2.24"/>
  <!-- interface-naming-policy project-wide -->
  <object class="GtkTextBuffer" id="textbuffer1">
    <property name="text" translatable="yes">                                         Tester Screen

 Build a glade file and save it in:
 configs/sim/gscreen/gscreen_custom

   The glade file must be called tester.glade
   The toplevel window must be called window1

 Then it can be launched from the linuxcnc launcher menu:
 sim/gscreen/gscreen_custom/tester 

 tester uses a handler file found in:
 share/gscreen/skins/tester/tester_handler.py

   tester_handler.py is a template of a 
   handler file for adding python code for
   more sophisticated customizations.

 If you wish to modify it for your screen it could be copied to:
 configs/sim/gscreen/gscreen_custom

 See the linuxcnc documentations on Gscreen for more information.
</property>
  </object>
  <object class="GtkWindow" id="window1">
    <property name="can_focus">False</property>
    <child>
      <object class="GtkTextView" id="textview1">
        <property name="visible">True</property>
        <property name="can_focus">False</property>
        <property name="buffer">textbuffer1</property>
      </object>
    </child>
  </object>
</interface>
